{
  "_comment": [
    "Criterion -> badge level, used to annotate .bestpractices.json into a",
    "browsable .bestpractices.jsonc ('make bestpractices-jsonc'), and to define",
    "the COMPLETE set of criteria the badge tracks so release-check can demand",
    "every one be answered.",
    "",
    "TWO criteria series live on the badge site and both appear in the answers:",
    "  * Metal series (OpenSSF Best Practices Badge) -- the lower_snake_case",
    "    keys -- graded 'passing' | 'silver' | 'gold'. Page:",
    "    https://www.bestpractices.dev/en/projects/13480/<level>",
    "    (the bare project URL is the passing view; /silver and /gold exist).",
    "  * OSPS Baseline (OSPS-XX-NN.NN keys) -- graded 'level 1' | 'level 2' |",
    "    'level 3'. Open the project's Baseline view and select that maturity",
    "    level; the full catalogue is also at https://baseline.openssf.org/.",
    "",
    "A criterion is listed at the LOWEST tier at which it first applies -- the",
    "page you open first to find it. Some criteria are restated (strengthened)",
    "at a higher tier; they still first appear on the level named here.",
    "",
    "'no_justification' lists criteria the badge form does NOT give a rationale",
    "field (prerequisite/derived answers). release-check exempts them from the",
    "'justification must be non-empty' rule; a status is still required.",
    "",
    "PROVENANCE -- regenerated by hand from the authoritative machine-readable",
    "sources, both from the main branch on 2026-07-14:",
    "  * metal: coreinfrastructure/best-practices-badge criteria/criteria.yml",
    "    (omap levels 0/1/2 -> passing/silver/gold).",
    "  * baseline: ossf/security-baseline baseline/OSPS-*.yaml (each assessment",
    "    requirement's 'applicability': maturity-1/2/3 -> level 1/2/3).",
    "Regenerate and re-verify when either source adds or moves criteria.",
    "check-bestpractices-levels.py fails the build if .bestpractices.json holds",
    "a criterion absent from the maps below."
  ],
